cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.SD, cs.DS

The paper deals with anonymization of social-network graphs, which involves privacy concerns and data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses privacy concerns, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes a new anonymization approach that involves perturbing the graph data, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) or cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves analyzing and drawing conclusions from the graph data, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
